Regress motion energy predictors from the emotion, arousal, aroval

The aim is to regress motion energy from the ratings RDM before calculating the RSA. Since the order of stimuli is different for each participant - and therefore the flattened RDM has a different order for every participant - the “easiest” thing to do is to treat motion energy as another ratings_type.

This will mean that in the calculated rdm df there will be also a (nested) column for motion_energy rdm. At this point we just need to regress motion_energy from emotion/arousal/valence/aroval and then calculate the RSA.

Motion energy was calculated here:

# 01: Calculate the motion energy
root_dir : /data00/leonardo/RSA/prep_scripts/07_motion_energy_movies/
script/nb : do_motion_energy.ipynb

# 02 : Generate an output which is compatible with the other <model_type>_ratings.csv
# in /data00/leonardo/RSA/analyses/RATINGS

do_motion_energy_compatible_with_ratings.Rmd

# The latter was done in R on the output of the python nb in order to keep mental
# sanity at the expense of efficiency

and saved into the file motion_energy_ratings.csv in /data00/leonardo/RSA/analyses/RATINGS.

Or course the motion energy estimates are not ratings, however after 1,000 requests of “Why don’t we do this and that…? It’s easy!” I had to give up consistency, again for the sake of mental sanity.

There are a few key modifications two do to make this work:

  • add motion_energy to the ratings_type (~ line 148)

  • after calculating the rdm’s, add some logic for the regression of motion energy.

Calculate RATINGS RDMs

# NB: ratings_type is now a *vector*, e.g.: 
# ratings_type <- c("emotion","arousal","valence","aroval")
# to test the fn below for one rating type : do_RDMs_rats("emotion")

do_RDMs_rats <- function(ratings_type, remove_neutrals) {

  ratings_type = ratings_type[1]
  
  ratings_path <- paste0(bd_ratings,"/",ratings_type,"_ratings.csv")
  rats <- read_csv(ratings_path)
  
  
  # ------- IMPORTANT : AVG ACROSS MOVIES FOR EMOTION PREDICTORS MODEL -----
  rats <- rats %>% 
    select(sub, emotion, high_low_code, starts_with("r_")) %>% 
    # ------ specific for emotion_high_low_predictors -----------
    mutate(emotion = paste0(emotion, "_", str_match(high_low_code, "high|low")) ) %>% 
    select(-high_low_code) %>% 
    # ------ specific for emotion_high_low_predictors -----------
    group_by(sub, emotion) %>% 
    reframe(across(starts_with("r_"), median, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
    ungroup %>% 
    arrange(sub, emotion)
  
  # ------- IMPORTANT : AVG ACROSS MOVIES FOR EMOTION PREDICTORS MODEL -----
  
  
  if (remove_neutrals == "YES") {
    rats <- rats %>% filter(!str_detect(emotion, "neutral"))
  }
  
  rdm <- rats %>%
    filter(sub %in% subs) %>%
    select(sub, starts_with("r_")) %>%
    group_by(sub) %>%
    nest %>%
    mutate(!!paste0("RDM_",ratings_type) := data %>% map(~ DDOS_vec(.x, dist_method_rating))) %>%
    ungroup %>% 
    # remove the sub with the prospect of merging rdms of different ratings/models
    select(!data)
  
  return(rdm)
  
}

# calculate rdms for all ratings_type and return one column for each ratings_type
RDMs_rats <- map_dfc(ratings_type, ~ do_RDMs_rats(.x, remove_neutrals)) %>%
  # remove the duplicated sub_ columns (generated by do_RDMs_rats) 
  janitor::clean_names() %>% 
  mutate(sub = sub_1) %>% 
  select(sub, starts_with("rdm"))

Cross-correlation matrix of all ratings RDMs - including motion energy

df <- RDMs_rats %>% unnest()
## Warning: `cols` is now required when using `unnest()`.
## ℹ Please use `cols = c(rdm_emotion, rdm_arousal, rdm_valence, rdm_aroval, rdm_motion_energy)`.
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(purrr)
library(stringr)
library(ggplot2)

# Step 1: Standardize columns starting with "rdm_"
df_std <- df %>%
  group_by(sub) %>%
  mutate(across(starts_with("rdm_"), scale)) %>%
  ungroup()

# Step 2: Calculate correlation matrix for each subject
# First, get unique subjects
subjects <- unique(df$sub)
corr_list <- list()

for (s in subjects) {
  # Filter data for this subject
  sub_data <- df_std %>% 
    filter(sub == s) %>%
    select(starts_with("rdm_"))
  
  # Calculate correlation matrix
  corr_mat <- cor(sub_data, use = "pairwise.complete.obs")
  corr_list[[s]] <- corr_mat
}

# Step 3: Stack all correlation matrices and apply Fisher's z-transformation
# Create an empty dataframe to store stacked correlations
stacked_corr <- data.frame()

# Loop through subjects and their correlation matrices
for (s in names(corr_list)) {
  # Convert matrix to long format
  m_long <- reshape2::melt(corr_list[[s]])
  # Add subject identifier
  m_long$sub <- s
  # Bind to the result dataframe
  stacked_corr <- bind_rows(stacked_corr, m_long)
}


# Apply Fisher's z-transformation
stacked_corr <- stacked_corr %>%
  mutate(z_value = 0.5 * log((1 + value) / (1 - value)))

# Step 4: Calculate mean z values across subjects
mean_z <- stacked_corr %>%
  group_by(Var1, Var2) %>%
  summarize(mean_z = mean(z_value, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")

# Convert back to correlation coefficient (r) for interpretation
mean_z <- mean_z %>%
  mutate(mean_r = (exp(2 * mean_z) - 1) / (exp(2 * mean_z) + 1))

# Reshape for heatmap
mean_mat <- reshape2::acast(mean_z, Var1 ~ Var2, value.var = "mean_r")

# Step 5: Create heatmap of mean correlation matrix
library(corrplot)
## corrplot 0.95 loaded
corrplot(mean_mat, method = "color", type = "upper", 
         tl.col = "black", tl.srt = 45,
         addCoef.col = "black", number.cex = 0.7,
         col = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(200),
         title = "Mean Correlation Matrix (Fisher Transformed)")

Regress out motion_energy

# Create a function to calculate residuals after regressing out rdm_motion_energy
regress_out_motion <- function(data, column_name, predictor_name) {
  formula <- as.formula(paste(column_name, "~", predictor_name))
  model <- lm(formula, data = data)
  return(residuals(model))
}

# Create new dataframe with residuals for each subject and each variable
df_reg <- df %>%
  group_by(sub) %>%
  group_modify(~{
    .x %>% mutate(
      rdm_emotion_res = regress_out_motion(.x, "rdm_emotion", "rdm_motion_energy"),
      rdm_arousal_res = regress_out_motion(.x, "rdm_arousal", "rdm_motion_energy"),
      rdm_valence_res = regress_out_motion(.x, "rdm_valence", "rdm_motion_energy"),
      rdm_aroval_res = regress_out_motion(.x, "rdm_aroval", "rdm_motion_energy")
    )
  }) %>%
  select(sub, rdm_emotion_res, rdm_arousal_res, rdm_valence_res, rdm_aroval_res) %>%
  ungroup()

Calculate FMRI RDMs

IMPORTANT : Since we already removed neutral from df_path_copes we don’t need to filter anything anymore here.

# Fn to calculate the rdm_fmri for one sub
# Test for one sub: do_RDM_fmri(subs[1], copes_numba, df_path_copes)

do_RDM_fmri <- function(sub_id, copes_numba, df_path_copes) {
  
  # load all the copes nii.gz into a df
  df_copes <- load_sub_copes(sub_id, copes_numba, df_path_copes)
  
  # the code below does the calculation of the tril of RDM_fmri for all rois for one sub
  
  one_sub_RDM_fmri <- tibble(
    sub = sub_id,
    roi = region_labels
  ) %>%
  
    # extract idx_roi for atlas voxels in that roi
    mutate(idx_roi = roi %>% map(~ which(atlas_nii == .x)) ) %>%
    
    # extract the df_copes for the voxels in that region (idx_roi)
    mutate(df_copes_region = idx_roi %>% map(~ df_copes[.x,]) ) %>%
    
    # calculate tril of RDM_roi (output as numeric vector)
    mutate(rdm_fmri = df_copes_region %>% map(~ DDOS_vec(t(.x), dist_method_fmri)) ) %>% 
    
    # select only sub, roi (numba) and RDM_roi
    select(sub, roi, rdm_fmri) 
  
  return(one_sub_RDM_fmri)
}

# Join fmri and rats RDMs and create a copy of the rat RDM for each sub/roi
RSA <- right_join(RDMs_fmri, RDMs_rats, by = "sub") %>%
  group_by(sub) %>%
  
  # Dynamically create rsa_ columns for every ratings type
  mutate(across(
    all_of(paste0("rdm_", ratings_type)),

  ) %>%

    ~ str_replace(.x, "rsa_rdm_", ""),

Calculate mean tril for ratings and for fmri (for each roi in the fmri case)

# Takes a df and a "column" containing a nested vector in each row
# and returns the element-wise mean of that vector across rows
get_elementwise_mean <- function(mydf, nested_col, fun=mean) {
  m <- matrix(
    mydf[[nested_col]] %>% unlist,
    nrow = nrow(mydf),
    ncol = length(mydf[[nested_col]][[1]]),
    byrow = TRUE
  )
  
  m_summary <- apply(m, 2, fun)
  return(m_summary)
}


# mean RDMs_rats
mean_RDMs_rats <- RDMs_rats %>% select(starts_with("rdm_")) %>% colnames %>%  
  map_dfc(~{
    mean_tril <- get_elementwise_mean(RDMs_rats, .x, fun = mean)
    tibble(!!.x := mean_tril)
  })

prepare_papaya <- function(atlas_filename, roi_numba) {
  
  f <- function(nii_filename) {
    return(paste0(bd_atlases,"/", nii_filename))
  }
  
  nii_atlas <- RNifti::readNifti( f(atlas_filename) )
  # view(nii_atlas)
  
  nii_atlas_thr <- ifelse(nii_atlas == roi_numba, 1, 0)
  RNifti::writeNifti(nii_atlas_thr, template = nii_atlas, paste0(bd_atlases,"/tmp_ROI.nii.gz"))
  
  papaya(
    c(f("Dummy.nii.gz"), f("MNI152_T1_2mm_brain.nii.gz"), f("tmp_ROI.nii.gz")),
    options = list(
      papayaOptions(alpha = 1, lut = "Grayscale"),
      papayaOptions(alpha = 0.5, lut = "Grayscale"),
      papayaOptions(alpha = 0.5, lut = "Red Overlay", min = 0, max = 5)
    ),
    interpolation = FALSE,
    orthogonal = FALSE
  )
  
}

Create the volumes with the RSA_mean

NB: a df RSA_volumes_df will be created, to be used in the shiny app to generate the actual temporary volumes

RSA_volumes_df <- ratings_type %>% map_dfc(
  ~ {
    nii <- atlas_nii %>% as.vector()
    
    for (ROI_numba in RSA_mean$roi) {
      idx_ROI <- which(nii == ROI_numba)
      val_ROI <- RSA_mean %>% filter(roi == ROI_numba) %>% select(starts_with(.x)) %>% pull
      nii[idx_ROI] = val_ROI
    }
    return( tibble(!! .x := nii) )
  }
)

# We save the following into /data00/leonardo/RSA/analyses/RSA_ROI_APP
# RSA
# RSA_mean
# atlas_filename
# mean_RDMs_fmri
# mean_RDMs_rats


create_filename_results <- function(atlas_filename, copes_type, remove_neutrals) {
  atlas_root <- str_replace(atlas_filename, ".nii.gz", "")

  if(str_detect(copes_type,"one_ev_per_movie")) {EV_abbr <- "_OEPM"}
  if(str_detect(copes_type,"emotion_predictors")) {EV_abbr <- "_EP"}
  if(str_detect(copes_type,"emotion_high_low_predictors")) {EV_abbr <- "_EHLP"}
  
  option_MN <- ifelse(str_detect(copes_type,"_minus_neutral"),"_MN","")

  option_NN <- ifelse(remove_neutrals == "YES", "_RN", "")
  
  nsubs <- paste0("_N",length(subs))
  
  results_filename <- paste0(atlas_root, EV_abbr, option_MN, option_NN, nsubs, "___ME_REG")
  return(paste0(bd_results,"/",results_filename,".RData"))
  
}

results_file <- create_filename_results(atlas_filename, copes_type, remove_neutrals)
results_file
## [1] "/data00/leonardo/RSA/analyses/RSA_ROI_APP/results_RSA_ROI/anatomy_toolbox_for_RSA_EHLP_RN_N26___ME_REG.RData"
# save the results
save(
  RSA, RSA_mean, atlas_filename, mean_RDMs_fmri, mean_RDMs_rats, df_path_copes, subs, RSA_volumes_df,
  file = results_file
)
